    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-22T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-22T10:00:00-05:00" n="233"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.796/450: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-22T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 22, 1941—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>354. For Clayton from Morgan.</p>
                <p>“Your 255, September 19<note n="70" xml:id="d233fn70">Not printed.</note> just
                    received. Never intended to sign the agreement with figures in blank but only to
                    [initial?] the text of the agreement with the Minister for Foreign Affairs for
                    signature later in Washington. Please see last paragraph of my letter of
                    September 2.<note n="70" xml:id="d233fn1">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0293" n="285" xml:id="pg_285"/>
                <p>Committee will not accept figure of $100,000 with two planes since it insists
                    upon a substantial ‘cushion.’ See my telegram no. 349, September 19.<note n="71"
                        xml:id="d233fn71">Not printed.</note> Please authorize 150,000 maximum
                    amount as originally authorized. Believed that actual payments to be made may be
                    substantially less.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
